						"title": "Renkbench relaunch",
						"text": "Currently the Renkbench is just running with static content from a node.js service, since my webhost has updated the PHP version.<br/>I took advantage of the resulting downtime to refactor my Workbench Javascript code and added some missing features like window resizing and scrolling by arrow buttons and scrollbar.<br/>The new node.js backend is set up and hosted on Microsof Azure. Accordingly, the build and deployment pipeline, feeded by the Github repository, is setup on Azure Devops.<br/><br/>Now, I can go on with the content and the next Renkbench features like the context menu.<br /><br />The current sources and project status are available on <a href=\"https://github.com/lachsfilet/Renkbench\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub</a>."
